So do you know this feeling?
Yes, it’s called boredom! But you will be glad to hear it is not so bad as the songs say.
It’s just like a small dip in the ocean, and it means our minds are refreshed just like our body is when we wash with water.
In this way, we can stay alert and focused and gain new discoveries.
Boredom helps maintain a healthy brain, but most of us don’t know how to do that.


Don’t be sad, and I’ll share some tips with you.
When you feel bored, you should try some classic hobbies, like singing, painting, cooking or even tending your garden or taking up a sport.
Don't forget that reading some books or newspapers
and going to the movies are all good ways to make you relaxed.


