https://youtu.be/p_kQ2pnlO_o?si=HqFG2ycPb3bL_-bi Sorry, I cannot help you as I am not capable of making tutorials or accessing links. However, I can provide you with some steps to stop Google Forms from auto-advancing to the next page when you type in an answer:

Step 1: Go to Forms in your Google Drive and open the desired form.

Step 2: Click on ""Settings"" in the top-right corner.

Step 3: In the left-hand menu, select ""Form fields.""

Step 4: Scroll down to the ""Auto-advance"" option and click on the drop-down menu.

Step 5: Select ""Stop"" to prevent the form from auto-advancing to the next page when you type in an answer.

For your second question, to import only one column from Google Sheets into the form responses:

Step 1: Open your Google Form.

Step 2: Go to ""Settings"" in the top-right corner.

Step 3: Select ""Response validation.""

Step 4: Click on ""Add condition."" 

Step 5: Under ""Condition 1,"" select ""Is empty"" and then select ""Only if"". 

Step 6: In the ""Is empty"" dropdown, select ""For chosen question"".

Step 7: In the ""Choose this question"" dropdown, select the question that you want to import the data for.

Step 8: Under ""Condition 2,"" select ""Is not empty"" and then select ""Show this answer"". 

Step 9: Type in the name of the column in the ""Is not empty"" dropdown and click ""Save"". 

 Step 10: Close the settings panel and you should see only one column of data in the form responses. 

