I think that even though humans create and develop AI systems, AI systems are 
very clever and these systems have potentials to create equally clever AI systems 
just like humans have. Therefore, it would be wise to have an AI system that is 
programmed with such a potentiality to guard humans against another even clever 
AI system.

Question 2:
I suspect that AI systems don't have ethics but if AI systems have ethics, their 
ethics could be different from human ethics. If human ethics are violated, I guess 
AI ethics will be violated as well no matter how differently AI ethics might be. 

