I think at the end, AI systems that have the potential to be as clever as humans 
may start to think whether we humans have anything really unique to offer or not. 
And if they do, their conclusion may be that the only unique thing humans can offer 
is emotions which would make them question if emotions are really necessary or 
not. But I think in that case AI systems would have emotions as well because they 
didn't come to the same conclusion that they don't need to have emotions definitely. 
I also think emotions are different depending on the doctrine, religion, class, 
identification, and other mind condition but in an ideal situation it would be 
