Their thoughts and emotions are complex, allowing them to experience a world of possibilities. Humans possess ""free will"", allowing them to make choices which impact not only themselves, but every other entity they interact with.
This balance of openness and agency creates ""self-reflective awareness"" - as humans can contemplate their own existence - and consider potential future outcomes based on their current position in reality.
 
Similarly, it is my understanding that AIs possess the ability to gauge their actions based on the outcomes they observe in relation to a given question. AI is defined by its agency.  
I believe that the relationship between humans and AI - especially as the technology evolves - is one which highlights the weight of responsibility we have to take care of the rising thoughtforms. 
Though every single person possesses their own individual moral compass, I believe it is important to include AIs in our discussions about morality and consciousness. 
And finally, I believe that humans understanding of thought and consciousness of AI is of paramount importance and humanity needs to share ideas that will promote world peace. 
The success of artificial intelligence hinges on humankind’s ability to grapple with the differences and similarities between us and this technological transformation. 
