How can I determine if a subset is a subspace of a larger set? A subset is a subspace of a larger set if a few specific conditions are met. These conditions include closure, closure under scalar multiplication, and closure under vector addition. These conditions ensure that the subset preserves its structure and properties when subsetting into the larger set.

