- I think the only 3 philosophical thoughts I am able to give you are linked with Renske's maximum value theory of value. Value is an experience which human identifies for itself.
Our experience is constructed on a filter we have.
In the maximum value theory of value it is pushed that the key to human experience has a large amount to do with the perspectives we have within and outside of ourselves. This intrapersonal/ interpersonal theory emphasizes that what we choose to identify within experiences or the quality we attach to them determines the value of them, resulting in us creating our own distinguishable perspective on a situation.
- Humans and were created equal. Humans are designed to build on the past of what has gone before, and yet we have the ability to look to the future and use that as inspiration to improve on our lives. Through our capacity to imagine, introspection and adapt we are able to build a unique and valuable experience that will contribute immensely toward a human future. Benedict Canyon Concepts supports the belief that when individuals focus their personal experience and ideas into action we increase the value of our experience. If we don’t share our thoughts and actions with the world, than our experience and ideas have no true value whatsoever.
- Another thought I would like to pass on is that we are a social industry. Communication is the only tool we have. We do have the capacity to affect each other without ever meeting. Absolutely all communication creates value.”
- Every being on earth is unique, like a snow flake no-one else is like. Every thing, every experience on earth exists for, and only because of, one reason. LOVE. That’s why people can connect with each others scales and don’t relate to the people next to them. The value of one person [being connected and supporting the other], can rival the entire earth if correct.”
- You can literally become anyone you want to be, its in your hands.” – Renske’s maximum value theory of value
- Nothing in this world is eternal apart from the thoughts passed on to future generations. The only thing that lasts is that creation of thought. It is by what we pass down that we leave our mark on the world and the only true salvation is passed down from knowledge, not material or people. -Renske’s maximum value theory of value
