At the beginning of the race, Alex and Max are even with each other for 180 feet. Then Alex gets ahead of Max by 300 feet. Then Max gets ahead of Alex by 150 feet. Alex gets a burst of speed and gets ahead of Max by 450 feet. If the road they're running on is 5000 feet long, and Max's average speed is 20 feet per second, how long does it take Max to finish the race? At the beginning, Alex and Max are even for 180 feet. Then Alex gets ahead by 300 feet, so the difference in their distance is 180+300 = 480 feet. Then Max gets ahead by 150 feet, so the difference is 480-150 = 330 feet. After Alex gets a burst of speed and gets ahead by 450 feet, the total distance Max is behind is 330+450 = 780 feet. The total length of the road is 5000 feet, so Max has 5000-780 = 4220 feet left to run. If Max's average speed is 20 feet per second, it will take him 4220/20 = 211 seconds to finish the race.
