Other things (if I wanted to) I would make. 
The voting system I'd change, since it doesn't really work out well. I mean, it takes years to convince people andargv that certain things are straight up wrong. 
I'd also make sure there'd be constant acts of global empathy. We have a charity called Make-A-Wish which exists to give sick kids their last-ditch wish. I wonder what they'd wish for...? Probably an extended video meeting with someone in particular! So simple things like Make-A-Wish-type charities that exist worldwide, to give people the one drop of hope they so badly need. 
And then finally, maybe one day I want to maybe help individual beings in most need of support. Those people who are shut down and unable to do anything for themselves. 
The main belief I stand for is that I'm for global unity. I'm sharing my ideas because I think it'll be good for society, but I'm for global unity and what's best for the world not just for myself, or for a small group of people like my friends. I wrote this because I think society needs such motivation, such moral vision. 
Lastly, there are only so many reasons to do it. But I don't think I'm necessarily sent to this world to be a world ruler. By the hardship of my circumstances I'm shown that a king's crown does not weigh up to the crown of heaven. Possibly one day I could be. 
Maybe I'm sent to this world to simply make it a better place, and find my place in the world - without meaning to be world ruler. 
But I have dreamt of being a world ruler. It helped me feel more safe, surprisingly, probably because of where we currently live. To me, I could handle overthrowing any dictator of the world and withstand such problems. 
But at the same time, I feel I've given most everyone a second life, even if doesn't apply to everyone.  
