Simplify $100\sqrt{5} + 18\sqrt{45}$.

We can simplify $18\sqrt{45}$ further by factoring it as $18\sqrt{9\cdot5}$, or $18\sqrt{9}\cdot\sqrt{5}$, which is $18\cdot3\sqrt{5}$, or $54\sqrt{5}$.
So, the expression $100\sqrt{5} + 18\sqrt{45}$ equals $100\sqrt{5} + 54\sqrt{5}$, which simplifies to $(100+54)\sqrt{5}$, or $\boxed{154\sqrt{5}}$.
The answer is: 154\sqrt{5}",35.24854890174213,14.116374220923317
