All people named Barry are nice, while only half of the people named Kevin are nice.  Three-fourths of people named Julie are nice, while 10% of people named Joe are nice.  If a crowd contains 24 people named Barry, 20 people named Kevin, 80 people named Julie, and 50 people named Joe, how many nice people are in the crowd? There are 24 people named Barry, and all of them are nice, so there are 24 nice people.
There are 20 people named Kevin, and only half of them are nice, so there are 20/2 = 10 nice people.
There are 80 people named Julie, and three-fourths of them are nice, so there are 80 * 3/4 = 60 nice people.
There are 50 people named Joe, and 10% of them are nice, so there are 50 * 10/100 = 5 nice people.
Therefore, there are a total of 24 + 10 + 60 + 5 = 99 nice people in the crowd.
#### 99
The answer is: 99 
