Mark and James need a total of 14 dice that are 12 sided to play their game.  Mark has a bag of 10 dice and 60% of them are 12 sided.  James has a bag of 8 dice and 75% of them are 12 sided.  How many dice will the boys need to buy to play their game? Mark has a bag of 10 dice and 60% of them are 12-sided, so he has 10 * 0.60 = 6 dice that are 12-sided.
James has a bag of 8 dice and 75% of them are 12-sided, so he has 8 * 0.75 = 6 dice that are 12-sided.
Together, Mark and James have 6 + 6 = 12 dice that are 12-sided.
They need a total of 14 dice that are 12-sided, so they need to buy 14 - 12 = 2 more dice.
#### 2
The answer is: 2 
