The unique ability that we (humans) were born with is that we have the power to look into the past to solve any problem, we have the ability to look into the future to prepare for the challenges ahead, or we can pick any person from the past to discuss with. When it comes to popularizing history, it is a very scientific-spiritual activity.

Science- the  study of everything around us.
Spirituality –  refers to a force which is usually non-physical and transcendent to this earth- any universe or higher power.

When in every party there are 3 people who are considered to be the best, most talented, most desirable, etc.,  a situation comes up where it is said that you can invite 3 people from the past (close or famous) for dinner. Comparing with food, it is like dining with your favorite actors or your own favorite famous people.

When we think of this, we get into the history of science, mathematics, with all the great humans of the past millennia.

What is the role of History?

History is like looking into the past, where there are so many great accomplishments of our ancestors. It's like a book that teaches us the value of life,  like imparting taste in food, or like teaching us to dance and sing, or guide us in our future endeavors. History is like food for the soul.

However, it is very simple, when we think of this, we will immediately think of names like Mahatma Gandhi, Ramanujam,  Stephen Hawking, Mahaavatar Babaji, etc. And inviting them is very simple.

The great challenge to any modern journalist, teacher, or most ambitious people, is to think beyond it.

Now, the challenge is to fine one of the greatest women of the great modern time - in the men's world –pick a second one from science- a Mathmatics genius and the third from politics- pick from the women who broke the glass ceiling.

I put my apprehensions aside, and I chose Kiran Bedi, Katherine Johnson, & General D S Hooda.

But why these 3?

Kiran Bedi: why?

For Physical fitness- Honoring Women-2018

Kiran bedi was India's first women IPS officer. She prepared and led teams for the 2018 Honoring Women Awards for physical fitness.

Kiran Bedi was the only Indian woman who has not only trained and led teams to achieve  second place at an Olympics event but she is also among seven women who have been certified as Master Swim Coaches by USA Water Polo. In 199",73.43669403679714,51.37482809828735
