Consider the function
\[ f(x) =
\begin{cases}
-x^2 & \text{if } x \geq 0,\\
x+8 & \text{if } x <0.
\end{cases}
\]Find $f(f(f(f(f(1))))).$ We start from the inside and work our way out.
$f(1) = -(1)^2 = -1.$
$f(f(1)) = f(-1) = -1 + 8 = 7.$
$f(f(f(1))) = f(7) = - (7)^2 = -49.$
$f(f(f(f(1)))) = f(-49) = -49 + 8 = \boxed{-41}.$
The answer is: -41 
