In 2011, The City of Philadelphia implemented the first of its kind Mentoring By Reading program in an effort to address the many challenges of the inner city community. Partners for a Promising America created an interactive reimbursement form to process paperwork to help teachers with “pay for play” funding from the Department of Education. A rock solid data database at the heart of the program, 360gen, became an engine for growth, providing powerful analysis and flexibility for the entire program. Throughout the world, the Mentoring By Reading program has helped put over 4000 children back on the path to literacy.

