If Alex purchases 110 feet of cable and distributes it equally among 11 security cameras, and he also buys 2 cameras per day for 8 days before running out of cable, what is the number of feet of cable that Alex used for each camera? Alex purchased 110 feet of cable and distributed it equally among 11 security cameras, so each camera received 110/11 = 10 feet of cable.
He also bought 2 cameras per day for 8 days before running out of cable, so he used 2*8 = 16 cameras in total.
Since each camera received 10 feet of cable, the total number of feet of cable used is 10*16 = 160 feet.
Therefore, Alex used 160 feet of cable for each camera.
