# The SPARCS Alliance

## The Readers View

The SPARCS Alliance is a youth coaching opportunity that expands the SPS of book publishing, education publishing, and fiction and non fiction publishing to library makerspaces across America.  

Parking slips like SPARCS destroy the ability of our students and other readers to have a full experience of learning and growing in subjects of importance. 1 in 200 students (who are lucky) have a chance to have experience that makes them able to look beyond what they don’t know.  They are standing so far away from what they don’t know they don’t even know it exists. The 99.9% miss out. These youth often aren’t healthy or are trying throughout their lives to rebuild their lives.  This group of people and others like it are beyond their means to go to the city library. The libraries are Vollgates (big farms) and the parking spots producers are in the way.

# The library learning makerspace

This opportunity is a open public space and like GertrudeAnce cycycle reuse and refill type management schema.

# The Library Learning Makerspace

> ""Library science is an extremely complex subject, but appears to assume false
simplifications."" from Wilhelm Dilthey, 1914

The library is a kind of park with both public and exclusive schooling as public lessons and private lessons, both public and private activity in between, and both private work and public work at the library.  The satisfaction that can be derived from being a makerspace center is essentially a building block of human social existence in a stable and civilized environment. Consider:

What could be better?  What is worth renouncing?  What are the things humans really need?  What makes humans most satisfied?  What needs can be created in us if we can step in and help out by influencing?  What gives us the strongest emotions and makes us fill up faster than any other activity?  What in our daily life, if we compared our lives with our creator's, is unacceptable now?  What calls to us and what is easily available?  What puts us at conflict and what is sustainable?  What will ensure the future leadership of humanity?

If you find the upper list to be important to you, notice that in fact it is what would happen if we would utilize the licensable library of knowledge and the",18.615693796645587,23.09028119526264
