Answer: Whitney did 4 loads of laundry, and each load takes 40 minutes to wash. So, for Whitney, 4 loads x 40 minutes per load = 160 minutes spent washing.

Alex did 7 loads of laundry, and each load also takes 40 minutes to wash. So, for Alex, 7 loads x 40 minutes per load = 280 minutes spent washing.

Adding Whitney's and Alex's washing times, we get 160 minutes + 280 minutes = 440 minutes spent washing.

For drying, both Whitney and Alex did 40 loads of laundry (4 by Whitney and 7 by Alex). Each load takes 25 minutes to dry. So, for drying, 40 loads x 25 minutes per load = 1000 minutes spent drying.

