naive,dinner_party,Pick a set of figures from history for your own special dinner party where you get to talk to them.,"Danielle: Hey filmmakers!
Danielle: You all sure said some good stuff about the class in our commentforms last week! X) So it’s a double statement from me...
Danielle: We’re ready for the new round and looking forward to getting your ideas!
Danielle: I just want to say thanks to David Winter, who is implementing your ideas from the last round.
Danielle: The second assignment is still a story generator: Make a living out of stories telling: A short film about a morning run freak!
Danielle: Think about what you would produce and who it would be produced by. It doesn’t matter if it’s you, if it’s your favourite character, or what. Have fun!
Danielle: Even if you can’t figure out a topic just yet, try to think about what would make a good option.
Danielle: The important thing is to find a start that hosts your interest.
Danielle: Melina and Laila will report on this class of fiction.
Danielle: Please enter your thoughts and recommendations on this in a comment. Or just tell us your current thoughts and problems we can help to solve.
Danielle: Preparing comments for the class director is your task. It would be great, if you could keep them fairly short but precise.
Danielle: Thereof, be precise in what you do and what your next steps in implementing your plan might look like.
Danielle: Let’s do this class together!
Danielle: Afterwards, there a lot of questions already waiting answers on thic forum, I recommend to read the replies from Melina and Laila and answer accordingly.
Danielle: Feel free to have your own article on thic forum.
Danielle: You start with your idea. Claire and David received an idea about how one can use the fact that our brains are composed of 70% water and turning your thoughts into real water. It’s a suit developed by a Californian, leading organic chemcis that you put on over your head for about five minutes before you go to bed, making your dreams come true. All you have to do is to imagine anything and the suit will put it into water so that your dreams will come true.
Danielle: As the chemist sees, people are perfectionless, dreaming about being perfect while being successful. The chemist made it into a possible science: People give water odor, so who has the water odor of success gets the chance to dream of being successful and the water odor of their dreams is what our brain gets.
Danielle: The scientist also had dreams of being someone else and being loved, as the production code with “I am not loved” in neon see through watermark on the outer leg shows. On the inside is written: ”Before I could walk, I used to crawl slowly over a concrete floor in a dimly-lit space, crawling past toys. My mother sat in a rocking chair, sewing a quilt",18.36794961790915,9.809023587426124
