What is the value of x if $\log_9(2x-7) = \dfrac{3}{2}$?
We want to solve $\log_9(2x-7) = \dfrac{3}{2}$.
Rewriting the equation in exponential form gives us $9^{\frac{3}{2}} = 2x-7$.
Since $9^{\frac{3}{2}} = (3^2)^{\frac{3}{2}} = 3^{3} = 27$, we have $27 = 2x-7$.
Simplifying, we find $2x = 34$, or $x = \boxed{17}$.
