Emma is 7 years old. If her sister is 9 years older than her and their brother is half their combined age, how old will their brother be when Emma turns 14? If Emma is 7 years old, then her sister is 7 + 9 = 16 years old.
The combined age of Emma and her sister is 7 + 16 = 23 years old.
Their brother is half their combined age, so he is 23 / 2 = 11.5 years old.
When Emma turns 14, their brother will be 11.5 + 7 = 18.5 years old.
So the boy is 18.5 years old when Emma turns 14.
#### 18.5
The answer is: 18.5 
