rofessionally. But I do know a lot of mathematics. What did you find most interesting as a kid? I was working very long hours, and I would've loved to have an assistant because I am an unsupervised kind of beast. It's a shame my biology went cool keeping around, 'cause you could work for 30 hours and not really have anyone to check in with. I love to talk about the things I'm doing. I want references. I'm getting more references, try that again. You can discuss anything that you want. So I get a diversity of requests which makes me really happy as an academic researcher. You got ask for them? Yeah, I suppose. I ask people. It is a question of getting to work faster. You know, when you get recognition, after a few months, you get all access to topics that are of course relevant. But other people",27.063194705479933,24.881456863913712
