 Jim spends 8 hours scuba diving.  In that time he finds a treasure chest with 100 gold coins in it.  He also finds 2 smaller bags that have half as much gold each.  How much gold does he find per hour? The two smaller bags each have half as much gold as the treasure chest, so they each have 100/2 = 50 gold coins.
In total, Jim finds 100 + 50 + 50 = 200 gold coins.
He spends 8 hours scuba diving, so he finds 200/8 = 25 gold coins per hour.
