A pre-trial calibration isn’t a bad idea. Ask, ""How many times have your said you have filed for divorce?"" and/or ""How many times have you yelled at me?""  
Compromise isn’t going to be a win, but sounding out the judge can get more hints and clues about how you’re spoken of out in public and behind your backs.
