4. Identify the basis of your decisions and re-evaluate them. 
5. Mourn the loss of your idealized relationship and move forward from there. 
6. Identify your emotional needs and communicate them clearly and calmly. 
7. Be compassionate to your spouse and empathetic to his emotions. 
8. Make an effort to avoid stressful topics and add humor and adventure into your marriage. 
9. Create opportunities for vulnerable conversations and tickle sessions. 
10. Grow closer to a God who can heal and whole you better than you can do yourself. 
11. Be self-aware and engaged in the help available to you. 
12. Don't let your emotions consume you. 
13. Try taking control of your time outside the home. 
14. Prioritize meaningful conversations with your spouse over taking personal time that should be spent together. 
15. Focus on godly growth in your marriage. 
16. Let go of your anger and make space for peace between you and your spouse. 
17. Practice gratitude in the small moments of your marriage. 
18. Try to limit your hopes and expectations. 
19. Clarify the moments in which you feel most connected. 
20. Create together time that changes into routine.  
21. Set boundaries, and rewrite the rules of your marriage. 
22. Be patient with the process. 
23. Focus on what your husband does well, and understand that each person has different gifts.  
