Me: I'm not doing this anymore. I've told you I'm fed up with you. You think I'm being slow but really you are the one who is taking everything way too slow.
Him: I still have hope we can work this out.
Me: How exactly do you propose me slowing down? No matter which way I slow down you can't get what you want.
Him: I want love that makes me happy.
Me: I gave you love that makes me happy but it seems you didn't want that. You wanted much more.
Him: I mistook. Now I see what I need.
Me: So you are okay with the fact that I am unhappy?
Him: I'm unhappy also. The situation is like this.
Me: If you are unhappy too why can't you do anything about it.
Him: Why do you not want to spend time with me. That's why I cannot do anything.
Me: It's not about time spent together. I don't need a partner who is such a pit of negative energy.
Him: Now you are just giving up.
Me: That's your problem.
Him: You never liked me.
Me: No, I thought you are the guy I could be with.
Him: Maybe I was. But.

